&gt; We use a bunch of static methods on various classes to provide
&gt; functionality.  Today I realized I have no idea how to mock these
&gt; classes.  Objects yes, classes no.
&gt;
&gt; Is there a good refactoring to fix this?
&gt;
&gt; Example:
&gt;
&gt; public class DbAccess {
&gt;     public static ResultSet query(DbQuery query) {
&gt;         // ...creates the necessary Db objects and returns a ResultSet
&gt; object.
&gt;     }
&gt; }
&gt;
&gt; If I want to mock the database access, I&#39;m going to need to either swap
&gt; DbAccess to DbAccessMock, or I&#39;ll need DbAccess.query() to redirect
&gt; through an interceptable (mockable) interface.
&gt;
&gt; Is there a standard refactoring for this?
